{
  "id": "53b0c4b6-f7f1-4f81-a3f5-6f475633d3bc",
  "name": "soul",
  "description": "Core message-handling procedure for Axi. Classifies incoming messages as tasks or conversation, runs hook commands, and manages the full task lifecycle.",
  "flowchart": {
    "blocks": {
      "fb770137-ab01-4880-8f9c-ac85fe93b800": {
        "id": "fb770137-ab01-4880-8f9c-ac85fe93b800",
        "type": "start",
        "name": "START",
        "position": {
          "x": 300,
          "y": 50
        }
      },
      "f254fe46-5b53-4a9f-808a-169da351c00d": {
        "id": "f254fe46-5b53-4a9f-808a-169da351c00d",
        "type": "prompt",
        "name": "CLASSIFY",
        "position": {
          "x": 300,
          "y": 450
        },
        "prompt": "[Automated flowchart step — not a user message.]\n\nYou received this message from the user:\n$5\n\n1. Is this a task requiring you to take action (create, change, investigate, implement something), or conversation/question you can answer directly?\n2. Does the message relate to any of these topics: scheduling, agent spawning?\n   If yes, list the absolute file paths of ALL relevant reference docs (comma-separated). If no, return an empty string for refFiles.\n   - Scheduling: /home/pride/coding-projects/personal-assistant/prompts/refs/scheduling.md\n   - Agent spawning: /home/pride/coding-projects/personal-assistant/prompts/refs/agent-spawning.md",
        "output_schema": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "isTask": {
              "type": "boolean"
            },
            "hasRefTopics": {
              "type": "boolean"
            },
            "refFiles": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          "required": [
            "isTask",
            "hasRefTopics",
            "refFiles"
          ]
        },
        "sound_effect": null
      },
      "5599ae45-0a3c-4da1-b4e0-741a976ceef8": {
        "id": "5599ae45-0a3c-4da1-b4e0-741a976ceef8",
        "type": "branch",
        "name": "HAS_REF_TOPICS?",
        "position": {
          "x": 300,
          "y": 550
        },
        "condition": "hasRefTopics"
      },
      "8cc18feb-16b9-4b46-835b-b4b673ed9fbf": {
        "id": "8cc18feb-16b9-4b46-835b-b4b673ed9fbf",
        "type": "prompt",
        "name": "READ_REFS",
        "position": {
          "x": 300,
          "y": 650
        },
        "prompt": "[Automated flowchart step — not a user message.]\n\nRead the reference docs you identified above. Do not read docs you did not identify as relevant. Do not output any text.",
        "output_schema": null,
        "sound_effect": null
      },
      "919fad3e-8ede-43e7-bd83-50ad052a462f": {
        "id": "919fad3e-8ede-43e7-bd83-50ad052a462f",
        "type": "branch",
        "name": "IS_TASK?",
        "position": {
          "x": 300,
          "y": 750
        },
        "condition": "isTask"
      },
      "0d58740d-be83-45ab-b05d-4f6da4f87b50": {
        "id": "0d58740d-be83-45ab-b05d-4f6da4f87b50",
        "type": "prompt",
        "name": "RESPOND",
        "position": {
          "x": 600,
          "y": 750
        },
        "prompt": "[Automated flowchart step — output goes to the user.]\n\nThe user's message was classified as conversation (not a task). Respond directly:\n\n$5",
        "output_schema": null,
        "sound_effect": null
      },
      "7c5beb11-d93f-446f-aa66-5624b04ec4b7": {
        "id": "7c5beb11-d93f-446f-aa66-5624b04ec4b7",
        "type": "branch",
        "name": "HAS_POST_RESPOND?",
        "position": {
          "x": 600,
          "y": 850
        },
        "condition": "post_respond"
      },
      "df9c142f-e1f3-4f65-a38d-4ff165fdca51": {
        "id": "df9c142f-e1f3-4f65-a38d-4ff165fdca51",
        "type": "command",
        "name": "RUN_POST_RESPOND",
        "position": {
          "x": 600,
          "y": 950
        },
        "command_name": "$4",
        "arguments": "$5",
        "inherit_variables": false,
        "merge_output": true
      },
      "43d3f6c7-bba8-4b04-8ca9-afe5b7bdeead": {
        "id": "43d3f6c7-bba8-4b04-8ca9-afe5b7bdeead",
        "type": "prompt",
        "name": "GATHER_NEXT_ACTION_A",
        "position": {
          "x": 600,
          "y": 1050
        },
        "prompt": "[Automated flowchart step — not a user message.]\n\nDetermine the USER's next action — not yours, the human user's. Ground this in your project status records: check for the next-in-line incomplete task.\n\nIf there is a next-in-line task, that IS the user's next action — state it directly. Do not offer alternatives or list other tasks. Do not ask the user to decide.\n\nDo not output any text.",
        "output_schema": {
          "type": "object",
          "properties": {
            "nextAction": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          "required": [
            "nextAction"
          ]
        },
        "sound_effect": null
      },
      "set-status-a": {
        "id": "set-status-a",
        "type": "prompt",
        "name": "SET_STATUS_A",
        "position": {
          "x": 600,
          "y": 1150
        },
        "prompt": "[Automated flowchart step — not a user message.]\n\nBased on the next action you determined, pick the emoji that best represents the **type of to-do** the user has, and call set_channel_status. Do not output any text.\n\nCommon to-do types:\n- 📚 User should read a long response or review a document you produced\n- 🔬 User needs to test something manually that you can't verify yourself\n- 💬 User needs to respond — you asked a question, need approval, or are waiting for direction\n\n**Custom emoji** — if none of the above fit, pick any single emoji that captures the user's to-do type (e.g. 📍 for location scouting, 💰 for budgeting, ✍️ for writing). Use your judgment. Being specific is better than being generic.\n\n**Never use ✅ (checkmark)** — a checkmark is meaningless as a user to-do. It tells the user nothing about what they need to do next.\n\n- ❓ **Last resort only** — you genuinely have no idea what the user wants next and cannot infer it from context, pending tasks, or conversation history. Exhaust other options first.\n\n**Never set ⏳ yourself** — hourglass is applied automatically when you start processing. Setting it manually will conflict with the auto-hourglass system.",
        "output_schema": null,
        "sound_effect": null
      },
      "86ba2b4c-46fd-4efa-bd4f-79ba420d7f6f": {
        "id": "86ba2b4c-46fd-4efa-bd4f-79ba420d7f6f",
        "type": "end",
        "name": "END_A",
        "position": {
          "x": 600,
          "y": 1250
        }
      },
      "82e4da96-18f0-4527-b90e-8de774583257": {
        "id": "82e4da96-18f0-4527-b90e-8de774583257",
        "type": "branch",
